title: Two critically injured in Palmerston North collision
content: Police are at the scene of the crash on Sunday morning (File photo).      Two people have been critically injured in a collision on the outskirts of Palmerston North.    The crash happened on a one-way bridge on Turitea Rd, south of Palmerston North, at 9.15am on Sunday, police said.    Two people - one from each car - were understood to be critically-injured.
